GLP1

Here you can see the medication used according to NHS. This results in 23198 prescriptions for 997 people.

#in bash
grep -E 'Byetta|Ozempic|Wegovy|Bydureon|Trulicty|Lixumia|Victoza|Rybelsus|Liraglutide|Dulaglutide|Exenatide|Lixisenatide|Semaglutide' gp_scripts.txt >glpfile.txt

We match on sex, DOB, and BMI at baseline and display characteristics of population before and after matching.

source("~/multistate2/code/utils.R")
prs_subset=readRDS("~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox-Personal/pheno_dir/prs_subset.rds")
#glp1=fread("~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox-Personal//glp1s.txt")

glp1=fread("~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox-Personal//glp1s_withi.txt")
colnames(glp1)[1]=c("Identifier")
colnames(glp1)[3]=c("event_dt")
df_baseline=readRDS("~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox-Personal/pheno_dir/output/dfukb_baseline.rds")
glp1$event_dt <- as.Date(glp1$event_dt, format="%d/%m/%Y")
unique_patients <- glp1 %>%
  group_by(Identifier) %>%
  summarize(script_date = min(event_dt))

m=merge(prs_subset,unique_patients,by = "Identifier",all.x = T)
m2=merge(m,df_baseline,by.x = "Identifier",by.y="identifier")

m2$treat=as.integer(ifelse(!is.na(m2$script_date),1,0))
library(MatchIt)

biomarkers=readRDS("~/Library/CloudStorage/Dropbox-Personal/ukbb-ehr-data/data/biomarkers.rds")
bmi=biomarkers[biomarkers$variable%in%"bmi",]
bmi$date <- as.Date(bmi$date, format="%Y/%m/%d")
sorted_data <- bmi %>%
  arrange(eid, date) %>%
  group_by(eid)  %>%
  slice(n())


names(sorted_data)=c("eid","date_last_bmi","variable","source","last_bmi")
m2=m2[!is.na(m2$f.21001.0.0),]
mg=merge(m2,sorted_data,by.x="Identifier",by.y="eid")
mg$bmi.prs=mg$BMI

start_before_enroll=which(mg$treat==1&difftime(mg$script_date,mg$f.53.0.0)<0)
length(start_before_enroll==1)
## [1] 50
## only 50
#mg=mg[-start_before_enroll,]
#last_bmi_before_script=which(mg$treat==1&difftime(mg$date_last_bmi,mg$script_date)<0)
#mg=mg[-last_bmi_before_script,]
# length(which(difftime(mg$date_last_bmi,mg$f.53.0.0,units = "days")<0))
# w=which(difftime(mg$date_last_bmi,mg$f.53.0.0,units = "days")>0)
# length(w)
# mg=mg[w,]

mg$diff=ifelse(mg$treat==1,difftime(mg$date_last_bmi,time2=mg$script_date,units = "days"),difftime(mg$date_last_bmi,time2 = mg$f.53.0.0,units = "days"))
sum(mg$diff<0&mg$treat==1)
## [1] 52
sum(mg$diff<0&mg$treat==0)
## [1] 35387
mg=mg[mg$diff>0,]

Now complete the matching based on f.34 (birth year)

matched=matchit(treat~f.34.0.0+f.21001.0.0+f.31.0.0,data=mg)
plot(summary(matched))

datm=match.data(matched)
summary(matched)

We now measure the percentage of BMI chance and calculate the influence of treatment, PRS, or the interaction:

Duration of treatment is the difference between last bmi and script date for treated and last bmi and enrollment for controls

ggplot(datm[datm$treat==1,],aes(as.numeric(diff)))+geom_histogram(binwidth = 50)+labs(x="Days Since Treatment")

ggplot(datm[datm$treat==0,],aes(as.numeric(diff)))+geom_histogram(binwidth = 50)+labs(x="Days Since Baseline in Controls")

datm$treatsincebase=difftime(datm[datm$treat==1,"date_last_bmi"],datm[datm$treat==1,"f.53.0.0"],units = "days")
ggplot(datm[datm$treat==1,],aes(as.numeric(treatsincebase)))+geom_histogram(binwidth = 50)+labs(x="Days Since Baseline in Treated")

Lets look at change in BMI (not proportional)

datm$delta=(datm$last_bmi-datm$f.21001.0.0)

your_model=lm(scale(delta)~treat+treat:bmi.prs,dat=datm,weights = weights)

Now lets look at some boxplots

  • By treatment
p <- ggplot(datm, aes(x=treat, y=delta,group=treat)) + 
  geom_boxplot()+labs(y="Change in BMI")

p

  • By treatment and PRS decile
datm$prs.group=cut(datm$bmi.prs,breaks = quantile(datm$bmi.prs,probs = seq(0,1,by=0.1)),labels = c(1:10))
p <- ggplot(datm, aes(x=prs.group, y=delta,group=prs.group)) + 
  geom_boxplot()+labs(y="Change in BMI")+facet_wrap(~treat)

p
